  "text": "As noted in the introduction, the analysis of [CITATION_1] predicted that, steady convection rolls should develop near the hot end for P r > 4, near the cold end for P r < 0.01, or at both end walls for 0.01 < P r < 4. Our results unequivocally contradict that prediction for Bo D = O(1). According to Fig. 6(b) , for P r 0.1 the wavelength of the pattern exceeds typical values of Γ x for any value of the the spatial attenuation rate s, so it makes no sense to discuss spatial localization. The dependence of the critical M a and λ on s for the stationary instability at P r = 0.1, 1, and 10 are shown in Fig. 8 ). We find that M a s c is a monotonically increasing function of s, regardless of the values of P r for Bo D = O(1), indicating that a stationary pattern always emerges first near the hot end wall.",
